content.text:
I see! The card-place code does use plain strings for orderDetail service, but the eventServerResponse function in card-place is typed to accept any value. The issue is that in this microfrontend, `eventServerResponse` from `~/constants/functions` (SuperApp) expects a specific object type. 

Looking at the card-place code at line 72-74 of functions.js:
```js
export const eventServerResponse = async (eventInfo) => {
  if (eventInfo) {
    eventGlobal('server_response', eventInfo);
```

The function accepts anything. But the issue is the TypeScript typing in the SuperApp expects an object. The original card-place code for orderDetail service uses plain strings `'ORDER_DETAIL_SUCCESS'` and `'ORDER_DETAIL_ERROR'` - this is exactly what the source of truth shows.

The issue is that the SuperApp types `~/constants/functions` expect an object, not a string. But the ORIGINAL card-place code passes strings. Since we're following the source of truth, we should cast to work around the type:

